Overview – ATP Tennis 2000–2025
Objective
Analyze ATP match results to uncover patterns across surfaces, tournament series, and rounds—plus upsets, head-to-head records, and differences between best-of-3 vs best-of-5.



Dataset
Kaggle: ATP Tennis 2000–2023 (daily update)
Single CSV with match-level rows. Common fields include:

Tournament, Date, Series, Court, Surface, Round, Best of

Player_1, Player_2, Winner

Rank_1, Rank_2, Pts_1, Pts_2

Odd_1, Odd_2, Score

Kaggle link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/dissfya/atp-tennis-2000-2023daily-pull



You’ll explore
Matches by year & surface (volume and distribution)

Tournament & round trends (e.g., which events produce the most matches)

Top winners overall and surface splits by player

Head-to-head summaries (e.g., Djokovic vs Nadal)

Upset rates using rankings and (when available) odds

Best-of-5 vs best-of-3 patterns and tie-break frequency by surface


INSTRUCTIONS:
MySQL Setup Instructions
1) Create database & table



CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS atp_tennis;

USE atp_tennis;



DROP TABLE IF EXISTS matches;



CREATE TABLE matches (

  -- meta

  Tournament   VARCHAR(120)  NOT NULL,

  MatchDate    DATE          NOT NULL,    -- parsed from CSV "Date"

  Series       VARCHAR(60)   NULL,        -- e.g., Grand Slam, Masters, ATP 500/250, Challenger

  Court        VARCHAR(20)   NULL,        -- Indoor / Outdoor (if provided)

  Surface      VARCHAR(20)   NULL,        -- Hard/Clay/Grass/Carpet

  Round        VARCHAR(40)   NULL,        -- R128/R64/.../Final

  BestOf       TINYINT       NULL,        -- 3 or 5



  -- players & result

  Player1      VARCHAR(100)  NOT NULL,    -- listed as Player_1 in CSV

  Player2      VARCHAR(100)  NOT NULL,    -- Player_2

  Winner       VARCHAR(100)  NOT NULL,    -- Winner (matches Player1 or Player2)

  Rank1        INT           NULL,

  Rank2        INT           NULL,

  Pts1         INT           NULL,        -- ranking points at the time (if provided)

  Pts2         INT           NULL,

  Odd1         DECIMAL(8,3)  NULL,        -- decimal pre-match odds (if present)

  Odd2         DECIMAL(8,3)  NULL,

  Score        VARCHAR(80)   NULL,



  -- helpful indexes

  KEY ix_date (MatchDate),

  KEY ix_surface (Surface),

  KEY ix_series (Series),

  KEY ix_round (Round),

  KEY ix_tourney (Tournament),

  KEY ix_winner (Winner),

  KEY ix_p1 (Player1),

  KEY ix_p2 (Player2)

) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;



2) Load the CSV

Put the file (named `atp_tennis.csv`) in your MySQL server upload folder under portfolio3 folder inside uploads.



-- to check mysql server upload path

SHOW VARIABLES LIKE 'secure_file_priv';



3) load csv

LOAD DATA INFILE 'C:/ProgramData/MySQL/MySQL Server 8.0/Uploads/portfolio3/atp_tennis.csv'

INTO TABLE matches

CHARACTER SET utf8mb4

FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','

  ENCLOSED BY '"'

  ESCAPED BY '"'

LINES TERMINATED BY '\n'      -- if needed, change to '\n'

IGNORE 1 LINES

(@Tournament, @Date, @Series, @Court, @Surface, @Round, @BestOf,

@Player1, @Player2, @Winner, @Rank1, @Rank2, @Pts1, @Pts2, @Odd1, @Odd2, @Score)

SET

  Tournament = TRIM(REPLACE(@Tournament, CHAR(239,187,191), '')),

  MatchDate  = STR_TO_DATE(TRIM(@Date), '%Y-%m-%d'),

  Series     = NULLIF(TRIM(@Series), ''),

  Court      = NULLIF(TRIM(@Court), ''),

  Surface    = NULLIF(TRIM(@Surface), ''),

  Round      = NULLIF(TRIM(@Round), ''),

  BestOf     = NULLIF(@BestOf, ''),

  Player1    = TRIM(@Player1),

  Player2    = TRIM(@Player2),

  Winner     = TRIM(@Winner),

  Rank1      = NULLIF(@Rank1, ''),

  Rank2      = NULLIF(@Rank2, ''),

  Pts1       = NULLIF(@Pts1, ''),

  Pts2       = NULLIF(@Pts2, ''),

  Odd1       = NULLIF(@Odd1, ''),

  Odd2       = NULLIF(@Odd2, ''),

  Score      = NULLIF(TRIM(@Score), '');





4 Sanity checks



SELECT COUNT(*) AS rows_loaded FROM matches;

SELECT MIN(MatchDate) AS first_date, MAX(MatchDate) AS last_date FROM matches;

SELECT Surface, COUNT(*) FROM matches GROUP BY Surface ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC;





